deploy().details: Emits a {DeployProxy} event. Requirements: - The caller must not have a proxy.

returns.proxy: The address of the newly deployed proxy.

deployAndExecute(address,bytes).details: Emits a {DeployProxy} and {Execute} event. Requirements: - The caller must not have a proxy. - `target` must be a contract.

returns.proxy: The address of the newly deployed proxy.

deployAndExecuteAndInstallPlugin(address.details: Emits a {DeployProxy}, {Execute}, and {InstallPlugin} event. Requirements: - The caller must not have a proxy. - See the requirements in `installPlugin`. - See the requirements in `execute`.

params.plugin: The address of the plugin to install.

returns.proxy: The address of the newly deployed proxy.

deployAndInstallPlugin(address).details: Emits a {DeployProxy} and {InstallPlugin} event. Requirements: - The caller must not have a proxy. - See the requirements in `installPlugin`.

params.plugin: The address of the plugin to install.

returns.proxy: The address of the newly deployed proxy.

deployFor(address).details: Emits a {DeployProxy} event. Requirements: - The user must not have a proxy already.

params.user: The address that will own the proxy.

returns.proxy: The address of the newly deployed proxy.

getMethodsByOwner(address,address).details: An empty array is returned if the plugin is unknown.

params.owner: The proxy owner for the query.

getMethodsByProxy(address,address).details: An empty array is returned if the plugin is unknown.

params.envoy: The address checked for permission to call the target.
params.owner: The proxy owner for the query.

params.envoy: The address checked for permission to call the target.

getPluginByOwner(address,bytes4).details: The zero address is returned if no plugin is installed.

params.method: The method selector for the query.
params.owner: The proxy owner for the query.

getPluginByProxy(address,bytes4).details: The zero address is returned if no plugin is installed.

params.method: The method selector for the query.

params.user: The user address for the query.

installPlugin(address).details: Emits an {InstallPlugin} event. Notes: - Installing a plugin is a potentially dangerous operation, because anyone can run the plugin. - Plugin methods that have the same selectors as {IPRBProxy.execute}, {IPRBProxy.owner}, and {IPRBProxy.registry} can be installed, but they can never be run. Requirements: - The caller must have a proxy. - The plugin must have at least one implemented method. - There must be no method collision with any other plugin installed by the caller.

params.plugin: The address of the plugin to install.

setPermission(address,address,bool).details: Emits a {SetPermission} event. Notes: - It is not an error to set the same permission. Requirements: - The caller must have a proxy.

params.envoy: The address of the account the caller is giving or taking permission from.

uninstallPlugin(address).details: Emits an {UninstallPlugin} event. Requirements: - The caller must have a proxy. - The plugin must be a known, previously installed plugin.

params.plugin: The address of the plugin to uninstall.

VERSION().notice: The release version of the proxy system, which applies to both the registry and deployed proxies.

constructorParams().notice: The parameters used in constructing the proxy, which the registry sets transiently during proxy deployment.

deploy().notice: Deploys a new proxy for the caller.

deployAndExecute(address,bytes).notice: This function performs two actions: 1. Deploys a new proxy for the caller 2. Delegate calls to the provided target, returning the data it gets back, and bubbling up any potential revert.

deployAndExecuteAndInstallPlugin(address.notice: This function performs three actions: 1. Deploys a new proxy for the caller 2. Delegate calls to the provided target, returning the data it gets back, and bubbling up any potential revert. 3. Installs the provided plugin on the newly deployed proxy.

deployAndInstallPlugin(address).notice: This function performs two actions: 1. Deploys a new proxy for the caller. 2. Installs the provided plugin on the newly deployed proxy.

deployFor(address).notice: Deploys a new proxy for the provided user.

getMethodsByOwner(address,address).notice: Retrieves the list of installed methods for the provided plugin.

getMethodsByProxy(address,address).notice: Retrieves the list of installed methods for the provided plugin.

getPermissionByOwner(address,address,add.notice: Retrieves a boolean flag that indicates whether the provided envoy has permission to call the provided target.

getPermissionByProxy(address,address,add.notice: Retrieves a boolean flag that indicates whether the provided envoy has permission to call the provided target.

getPluginByOwner(address,bytes4).notice: Retrieves the address of the plugin installed for the provided method selector.

getPluginByProxy(address,bytes4).notice: Retrieves the address of the plugin installed for the provided method selector.

getProxy(address).notice: Retrieves the proxy for the provided user.

installPlugin(address).notice: Installs the provided plugin on the caller's proxy, and saves the list of methods implemented by the plugin so that they can be referenced later.

setPermission(address,address,bool).notice: Gives or takes a permission from an envoy to call the provided target and function selector on behalf of the caller's proxy.

uninstallPlugin(address).notice: Uninstalls the plugin from the caller's proxy, and removes the list of methods originally implemented by the plugin.
